{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775867665131,"sessionID":"ses_28609f618ffe4b3DGYsb2Pncn2","part":{"id":"prt_d79f61ae7001DP9svlbOtiyWPr","messageID":"msg_d79f615c0001l7hbs13yhmfMk9","sessionID":"ses_28609f618ffe4b3DGYsb2Pncn2","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867722103,"sessionID":"ses_28609f618ffe4b3DGYsb2Pncn2","part":{"id":"prt_d79f626a1001CRkAFBqNrVNQVY","messageID":"msg_d79f615c0001l7hbs13yhmfMk9","sessionID":"ses_28609f618ffe4b3DGYsb2Pncn2","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_d56d44bb6c734f7fa5b6f96f","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## Overview\n\nPython SDK 使用 `requests.Session` 作为 HTTP 通信基础，通过 `HTTPAdapter` 实现连接池管理。本 spec 定义 HTTP 客户端的创建、配置、请求发送和生命周期管理。\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: HTTP Session 创建与配置\n\n系统 SHALL 提供 `create_session` 工具函数，返回配置好连接池的 `requests.Session` 实例。\n\n#### Scenario: 默认连接池参数\n- **GIVEN** 调用 `create_session()` 无参数\n- **WHEN** session 创建完成\n- **THEN** `http://` 和 `https://` 前缀均挂载 `HTTPAdapter(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)`\n\n#### Scenario: 自定义连接池参数\n- **GIVEN** 调用 `create_session(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=50)`\n- **WHEN** session 创建完成\n- **THEN** 两个 adapter 均使用传入的 pool 参数\n\n### Requirement: Control Plane HTTP 客户端\n\n系统 SHALL 使用 `requests.Session` 与 Workload Manager 通信，支持 Bearer Token 认证。\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL 解析优先级\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.__init__(workload_manager_url=None, auth_token=None)`\n- **WHEN** 客户端初始化\n- **THEN** `base_url` 从环境变量 `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` 读取；若均未设置则为 `None`\n\n#### Scenario: Auth Token 从 ServiceAccount 文件读取\n- **GIVEN** `auth_token` 参数为空字符串或 `None`\n- **WHEN** 客户端初始化\n- **THEN** 尝试从 `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` 读取 token；文件不存在时返回空字符串\n\n#### Scenario: Authorization Header 设置\n- **GIVEN** token 非空\n- **WHEN** session 初始化\n- **THEN** `session.headers[\"Authorization\"]` 设置为 `\"Bearer {token}\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Authorization Header 省略\n- **GIVEN** token 为空字符串\n- **WHEN** session 初始化\n- **THEN** `session.headers` 不包含 `Authorization` 字段\n\n#### Scenario: Content-Type 默认头\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` 初始化完成\n- **WHEN** 检查 session headers\n- **THEN** `session.headers[\"Content-Type\"]` 为 `\"application/json\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Create Session 请求\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"ns\", ttl=7200, metadata={\"key\": \"val\"})`\n- **WHEN** 发送请求\n- **THEN** `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter`，body 为 `{\"name\": \"test\", \"namespace\": \"ns\", \"ttl\": 7200, \"metadata\": {\"key\": \"val\"}}`\n\n#### Scenario: Create Session 响应解析\n- **GIVEN** 服务端返回 `{\"data\": {\"sessionId\": \"abc-123\"}}`\n- **WHEN** `create_session` 解析响应\n- **THEN** 返回 `\"abc-123\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Create Session 缺少 sessionId\n- **GIVEN** 服务端返回 `{\"data\": {}}`\n- **WHEN** `create_session` 解析响应\n- **THEN** 抛出 `ValueError`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete Session 404 视为成功\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"nonexistent\")` 返回 HTTP 404\n- **WHEN** 方法处理响应\n- **THEN** 返回 `True`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete Session 其他错误\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"id\")` 返回 HTTP 500\n- **WHEN** 方法处理响应\n- **THEN** 记录警告日志并返回 `False`\n\n#### Scenario: 请求超时元组\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`\n- **WHEN** 发送任何请求\n- **THEN** `timeout` 参数为 `(5.0, 120)`\n\n#### Scenario: Close 释放 session\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.close()` 被调用\n- **WHEN** 方法执行\n- **THEN** `self.session.close()` 被调用\n\n### Requirement: Data Plane HTTP 客户端 (Code Interpreter)\n\n系统 SHALL 使用 Router-relative URL 路径与 Code Interpreter 数据面通信。\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL 从 Router URL 构建\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:8080\", namespace=\"ns\", cr_name=\"my-interpreter\")`\n- **WHEN** 客户端初始化\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` 为 `\"http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/ns/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL 显式传入\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://custom/url/\")`\n- **WHEN** 客户端初始化\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` 为 `\"http://custom/url/\"`，忽略 `router_url`/`namespace`/`cr_name`\n\n#### Scenario: Session Header 设置\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"sess-1\")`\n- **WHEN** 客户端初始化\n- **THEN** `session.headers[\"x-agentcube-session-id\"]` 为 `\"sess-1\"`\n\n#### Scenario: _request 发送 JSON body\n- **GIVEN** `_request(\"POST\", \"api/execute\", body=b'{\"cmd\": \"ls\"}')`\n- **WHEN** 请求发送\n- **THEN** `Content-Type: application/json` 设置在该请求上，URL 为 `urljoin(self.base_url, \"api/execute\")`\n\n#### Scenario: _request 无 body\n- **GIVEN** `_request(\"GET\", \"api/files\")`\n- **WHEN** 请求发送\n- **THEN** 不设置 `Content-Type` 请求头（使用 session 默认头）\n\n#### Scenario: Execute Command 超时缓冲\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=10.0)`\n- **WHEN** 构建请求\n- **THEN** HTTP read timeout 为 `12.0`（`timeout + 2.0`），body 中 timeout 字段为 `\"10s\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Execute Command 默认超时\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"ls\", timeout=None)`\n- **WHEN** 构建请求\n- **THEN** 使用 `self.timeout`（默认 120）作为超时基准\n\n#### Scenario: Execute Command 非零退出码\n- **GIVEN** 响应 JSON 为 `{\"exit_code\": 1, \"stderr\": \"error\", \"stdout\": \"\"}`\n- **WHEN** 解析响应\n- **THEN** 抛出 `CommandExecutionError(exit_code=1, stderr=\"error\", command=\"ls\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Run Code Python 语言\n- **GIVEN** `run_code(\"python\", \"print('hi')\")`\n- **WHEN** 方法执行\n- **THEN** 先 `write_file` 写入带时间戳的 `.py` 文件，再 `execute_command(\"python3 <file>\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Write File Base64 编码\n- **GIVEN** `write_file(\"hello\", \"/tmp/test.txt\")`\n- **WHEN** 发送请求\n- **THEN** POST `api/files`，body 为 `{\"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"content\": \"<base64>\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Upload File 多部分表单\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file(\"/local/file.txt\", \"/remote/path.txt\")`\n- **WHEN** 发送请求\n- **THEN** POST `api/files`，`files={'file': open('/local/file.txt', 'rb')}`，`data={'path': '/remote/path.txt', 'mode': '0644'}`，header 包含 `x-agentcube-session-id`\n\n#### Scenario: Download File 流式读取\n- **GIVEN** `download_file(\"/remote/path.txt\", \"/local/out.txt\")`\n- **WHEN** 发送请求\n- **THEN** GET `api/files/remote/path.txt`（`lstrip(\"/\")`），`stream=True`，逐块写入本地文件\n\n#### Scenario: List Files 查询参数\n- **GIVEN** `list_files(\"/some/path\")`\n- **WHEN** 发送请求\n- **THEN** GET `api/files?path=/some/path`\n\n#### Scenario: Clean Path 去除前导斜杠\n- **GIVEN** `remote_path = \"/absolute/path.txt\"`\n- **WHEN** 构建 download URL\n- **THEN** `clean_path` 为 `\"absolute/path.txt\"`\n\n### Requirement: Data Plane HTTP 客户端 (Agent Runtime)\n\n系统 SHALL 通过 Router 与 Agent Runtime 通信，支持 session bootstrap 和 invoke。\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL 构建\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:8080\", namespace=\"ns\", agent_name=\"my-agent\")`\n- **WHEN** 客户端初始化\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` 为 `\"http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/ns/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/\"`\n\n#### Scenario: SESSION_HEADER 常量\n- **GIVEN** 类定义\n- **WHEN** 访问 `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.SESSION_HEADER`\n- **THEN** 值为 `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap Session ID 成功\n- **GIVEN** GET `{base_url}` 返回响应头包含 `x-agentcube-session-id: \"new-session\"`\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` 执行\n- **THEN** 返回 `\"new-session\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap Session ID 缺失头\n- **GIVEN** GET `{base_url}` 返回响应不包含 `x-agentcube-session-id`\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` 执行\n- **THEN** 抛出 `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke 设置 Session Header\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"s1\", payload={\"msg\": \"hello\"})`\n- **WHEN** 发送请求\n- **THEN** POST `{base_url}`，headers 包含 `x-agentcube-session-id: s1` 和 `Content-Type: application/json`，body 为 JSON `{\"msg\": \"hello\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke 超时元组\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(\"s1\", payload, timeout=None)`，`connect_timeout=5.0`，`self.timeout=120`\n- **WHEN** 发送请求\n- **THEN** `timeout` 为 `(5.0, 120)`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke 自定义超时\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(\"s1\", payload, timeout=60.0)`\n- **WHEN** 发送请求\n- **THEN** `timeout` 为 `(5.0, 60.0)`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke 未初始化 session_id\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` 为 `None` 或空字符串\n- **WHEN** `invoke` 被调用\n- **THEN** 抛出 `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n\n### Requirement: 连接池复用\n\n系统 SHALL 在每个 HTTP 客户端实例中复用 `requests.Session`，避免重复创建连接。\n\n#### Scenario: 同一 Session 多次请求\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` 创建后调用 `create_session` 和 `delete_session`\n- **WHEN** 两次请求发出\n- **THEN** 使用同一个 `self.session` 实例\n\n#### Scenario: 多个客户端独立 Session\n- **GIVEN** 创建两个 `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` 实例\n- **WHEN** 检查 session 对象\n- **THEN** 两个实例的 `self.session` 是不同对象\n\n### Requirement: 工具函数\n\n系统 SHALL 提供日志、Token 读取等辅助函数。\n\n#### Scenario: read_token_from_file 成功\n- **GIVEN** 文件 `/tmp/token` 内容为 `\"my-token\\n\"`\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/tmp/token\")` 调用\n- **THEN** 返回 `\"my-token\"`\n\n#### Scenario: read_token_from_file 文件不存在\n- **GIVEN** 文件 `/tmp/nonexistent` 不存在\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/tmp/nonexistent\")` 调用\n- **THEN** 返回 `\"\"`\n\n#### Scenario: get_logger 创建 logger\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"test_module\", level=\"DEBUG\")`\n- **WHEN** 函数执行\n- **THEN** 返回名为 `\"test_module\"` 的 Logger，level 为 `DEBUG`\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775867722096,"end":1775867722102}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775867722175,"sessionID":"ses_28609f618ffe4b3DGYsb2Pncn2","part":{"id":"prt_d79f6f9ae0013I5feobZ1E7cCz","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d79f615c0001l7hbs13yhmfMk9","sessionID":"ses_28609f618ffe4b3DGYsb2Pncn2","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":25610,"input":22473,"output":2990,"reasoning":147,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.011381735}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775867723476,"sessionID":"ses_28609f618ffe4b3DGYsb2Pncn2","part":{"id":"prt_d79f6fed1001OTrcsbz36m9oLp","messageID":"msg_d79f6f9d6001Fu6G4kEqQIygUC","sessionID":"ses_28609f618ffe4b3DGYsb2Pncn2","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867725317,"sessionID":"ses_28609f618ffe4b3DGYsb2Pncn2","part":{"id":"prt_d79f7020b001nxkA2ORdjMAgGF","messageID":"msg_d79f6f9d6001Fu6G4kEqQIygUC","sessionID":"ses_28609f618ffe4b3DGYsb2Pncn2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_fe3ce46939c842a2b6de07bb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-026: K8s/AgentCube Provider — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `deployment/client-go.md`\n9: \n10: ## Scope\n11: \n12: This delta spec covers `KubernetesProvider` and `AgentCubeProvider` classes — their deployment, status retrieval, namespace management, name sanitization, CRD availability checks, and K8s client initialization error handling. Provider selection in CLI publish/status/invoke commands is also specified.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## KubernetesProvider\n17: \n18: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider constructor\n19: The system SHALL initialize `KubernetesProvider` with namespace, verbose flag, and optional kubeconfig path.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: default constructor\n22: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider()` is called with no arguments\n23: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n24: - **THEN** `namespace` SHALL default to `\"default\"`, `verbose` to `False`, and `kubeconfig` to `None`\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: custom kubeconfig\n27: - **GIVEN** a custom kubeconfig path is provided\n28: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n29: - **THEN** the system SHALL load the K8s configuration from that path\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: kubeconfig not found\n32: - **GIVEN** no kubeconfig file exists at the default or specified path\n33: - **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider` is initialized\n34: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise an exception indicating kubeconfig is missing\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: invalid kubeconfig\n37: - **GIVEN** a kubeconfig file exists but contains invalid YAML or cluster config\n38: - **WHEN** the provider is initialized\n39: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise an exception with the parsing or connection error\n40: \n41: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider._ensure_namespace\n42: The system SHALL create the target namespace if it does not already exist before deploying resources.\n43: \n44: #### Scenario: namespace already exists\n45: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider` is initialized with `namespace=\"default\"`\n46: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace` is called\n47: - **THEN** the system SHALL detect the namespace exists and take no action\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: namespace does not exist\n50: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider` is initialized with `namespace=\"my-agents\"`\n51: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace` is called and the namespace is not found\n52: - **THEN** the system SHALL create the namespace via the K8s API and log the creation\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: namespace creation failure\n55: - **GIVEN** the user lacks RBAC permissions to create namespaces\n56: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace` is called for a non-existent namespace\n57: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise an exception with the K8s API error surfaced to the caller\n58: \n59: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent\n60: The system SHALL deploy an agent as a standard K8s Deployment + NodePort Service.\n61: \n62: #### Scenario: full deploy flow\n63: - **GIVEN** valid `agent_name`, `image_url`, `port`\n64: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent` is called\n65: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n66:   1. Call `_ensure_namespace`\n67:   2. Call `_create_deployment`\n68:   3. Call `_create_service`\n69:   4. Call `wait_for_deployment_ready(..., timeout=120)`\n70:   5. Return result including `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, `service_url` as `http://localhost:{node_port}`\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider._create_deployment\n73: The system SHALL create or patch a Kubernetes `Deployment` with the agent container spec.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: create new deployment\n76: - **GIVEN** no existing deployment with the given name\n77: - **WHEN** `_create_deployment` is called with `name`, `image_url`, `port`, `replicas`, and optional `env_vars`\n78: - **THEN** the system SHALL create a `Deployment` with:\n79:   - `metadata.name` = sanitized name\n80:   - `spec.replicas` = provided replicas (default 1)\n81:   - `spec.template.spec.containers[0].image` = `image_url`\n82:   - `spec.template.spec.containers[0].ports[0].containerPort` = `port`\n83:   - `spec.template.spec.containers[0].env` populated from `env_vars` if provided\n84:   - `spec.template.spec.containers[0].command` set from `entrypoint` if provided\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: patch existing deployment\n87: - **GIVEN** a deployment with the given name already exists\n88: - **WHEN** `_create_deployment` is called with updated `image_url` or `replicas`\n89: - **THEN** the system SHALL patch the existing deployment with the new spec\n90: \n91: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider._create_service\n92: The system SHALL create or patch a `NodePort` `Service` to expose the deployment.\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: create NodePort service with auto-assigned port\n95: - **GIVEN** `node_port` is `None`\n96: - **WHEN** `_create_service` is called with `name` and `port`\n97: - **THEN** the system SHALL create a `Service` of type `NodePort` with K8s auto-assigned node port in range 30000-32767\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: create NodePort service with explicit port\n100: - **GIVEN** `node_port` is provided (e.g., `30080`)\n101: - **WHEN** `_create_service` is called\n102: - **THEN** the system SHALL create a `Service` with `spec.ports[0].nodePort` = the provided value\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: invalid NodePort range\n105: - **GIVEN** `node_port` is outside 30000-32767\n106: - **WHEN** `_create_service` is called\n107: - **THEN** the K8s API SHALL reject the request and the system SHALL surface the error\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider.wait_for_deployment_ready\n110: The system SHALL poll the deployment until all replicas are ready or timeout is exceeded.\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: deployment becomes ready\n113: - **GIVEN** a deployment is rolling out\n114: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` is called and pods become ready within timeout\n115: - **THEN** the system SHALL return successfully\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: deployment timeout\n118: - **GIVEN** a deployment name\n119: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` exceeds `timeout` seconds (default `120`)\n120: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `TimeoutError`\n121: \n122: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status\n123: The system SHALL retrieve the current status of a deployed agent including pod health.\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: agent running with ready pods\n126: - **GIVEN** a deployment exists with all replicas ready\n127: - **WHEN** `get_agent_status` is called with `agent_name`\n128: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a dict containing `status: \"running\"`, `replicas`, `ready_replicas`, and pod details\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: agent deployment not found\n131: - **GIVEN** no deployment exists with the given name\n132: - **WHEN** `get_agent_status` is called\n133: - **THEN** the system SHALL return `{\"status\": \"not_found\"}` or raise an appropriate exception\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: agent in rollout progress\n136: - **GIVEN** a deployment exists but not all replicas are ready\n137: - **WHEN** `get_agent_status` is called\n138: - **THEN** the system SHALL return status indicating rollout in progress with `ready_replicas < replicas`\n139: \n140: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider.delete_agent\n141: The system SHALL delete a deployment and its service, ignoring 404s on individual deletes.\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: successful deletion\n144: - **GIVEN** `delete_agent` is called with an existing agent name\n145: - **WHEN** deletion completes\n146: - **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\", \"namespace\"}` ignoring 404 on individual deletes\n147: \n148: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider._sanitize_name\n149: The system SHALL sanitize agent names to be valid Kubernetes resource names.\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: valid name unchanged\n152: - **GIVEN** a name containing only lowercase alphanumeric characters and hyphens\n153: - **WHEN** `_sanitize_name` is called\n154: - **THEN** the system SHALL return the name unchanged\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: invalid characters replaced\n157: - **GIVEN** a name containing uppercase letters, underscores, or other invalid characters\n158: - **WHEN** `_sanitize_name` is called\n159: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a name with invalid characters replaced (e.g., lowercased, underscores → hyphens)\n160: \n161: ---\n162: \n163: ## AgentCubeProvider\n164: \n165: ### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider constructor\n166: The system SHALL initialize `AgentCubeProvider` with namespace, verbose flag, and optional kubeconfig path.\n167: \n168: #### Scenario: default constructor\n169: - **GIVEN** `AgentCubeProvider()` is called with no arguments\n170: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n171: - **THEN** `namespace` SHALL default to `\"default\"`, `verbose` to `False`, and `kubeconfig` to `None`\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: cluster unreachable\n174: - **GIVEN** kubeconfig is valid but the cluster API server is unreachable\n175: - **WHEN** any provider method makes a K8s API call\n176: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise a connection error surfaced via CLI `_handle_error`\n177: \n178: ### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider._ensure_namespace\n179: The system SHALL ensure the target namespace exists before creating AgentRuntime CRs.\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: namespace created for CR deployment\n182: - **GIVEN** `AgentCubeProvider` is initialized with a non-default namespace\n183: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace` is called and namespace does not exist\n184: - **THEN** the system SHALL create the namespace before proceeding with CR operations\n185: \n186: ### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime\n187: The system SHALL create or patch an `AgentRuntime` custom resource with full spec.\n188: \n189: CR API: `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `version=\"v1alpha1\"`, `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`.\n190: \n191: #### Scenario: create AgentRuntime CR with all fields\n192: - **GIVEN** valid metadata with `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, readiness probe config\n193: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime` is called with `agent_name`, `image_url`, `port`, `entrypoint`, `env_vars`, and probe settings\n194: - **THEN** the system SHALL create an `AgentRuntime` CR with:\n195:   - `spec.image` = `image_url`\n196:   - `spec.port` = `port`\n197:   - `spec.entrypoint` = `entrypoint` if provided\n198:   - `spec.env` = merged from `env_vars` + `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` + `ROUTER_URL` (from params or environment)\n199:   - `spec.readinessProbe` with `httpGet.path` and `httpGet.port` from probe settings\n200:   - `spec.sessionTimeout` = `\"15m\"`\n201:   - `spec.maxSessionDuration` = `\"8h\"`\n202:   - `spec.imagePullSecrets` = `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: patch existing AgentRuntime CR\n205: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` CR with the given name already exists\n206: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime` is called with updated fields\n207: - **THEN** the system SHALL patch the existing CR with the new spec\n208: \n209: #### Scenario: missing readiness probe fields\n210: - **GIVEN** metadata lacks `readiness_probe_path` or `readiness_probe_port`\n211: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime` is called\n212: - **THEN** the system SHALL either use defaults or omit the readiness probe from the CR spec\n213: \n214: #### Scenario: environment variable fallback\n215: - **GIVEN** `env_vars` does not contain `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` or `ROUTER_URL`\n216: - **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime` runs\n217: - **THEN** the system SHALL read `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` / `ROUTER_URL` from the process environment and inject them into the CR spec\n218: \n219: ### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider._sanitize_name\n220: The system SHALL sanitize names for AgentRuntime CR resource naming.\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: CR name sanitization\n223: - **GIVEN** an agent name with invalid K8s characters\n224: - **WHEN** `_sanitize_name` is called\n225: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a DNS-1123 compliant name suitable for CR `metadata.name`\n226: \n227: ### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime\n228: The system SHALL retrieve an existing AgentRuntime CR by name and namespace.\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: CR exists\n231: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` CR exists with the given name in the namespace\n232: - **WHEN** `get_agent_runtime` is called\n233: - **THEN** the system SHALL return the CR object as a dict\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: CR not found\n236: - **GIVEN** no `AgentRuntime` CR exists with the given name\n237: - **WHEN** `get_agent_runtime` is called\n238: - **THEN** the system SHALL return `None`\n239: \n240: ### Requirement: CRD availability check\n241: The system SHALL verify that the AgentRuntime CRD is installed before attempting CR operations.\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: CRD not installed\n244: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` but the `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` CRD is not registered\n245: - **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider` attempts to create or get a CR\n246: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise an error indicating the CRD is not installed\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: CRD installed and accessible\n249: - **GIVEN** the CRD is registered and the user has RBAC permissions\n250: - **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider` performs CR operations\n251: - **THEN** the system SHALL succeed in creating/reading/updating AgentRuntime CRs\n252: \n253: ---\n254: \n255: ## Provider Selection in CLI Commands\n256: \n257: ### Requirement: Publish provider routing\n258: The system SHALL route publish operations to the correct provider based on `--provider`.\n259: \n260: #### Scenario: publish with --provider agentcube\n261: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish --provider agentcube`\n262: - **WHEN** the publish command executes\n263: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `AgentCubeProvider` and call `deploy_agent_runtime`\n264: \n265: #### Scenario: publish with --provider k8s\n266: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish --provider k8s`\n267: - **WHEN** the publish command executes\n268: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `KubernetesProvider` and call `deploy_agent` with `replicas` from options\n269: \n270: ### Requirement: Status provider routing\n271: The system SHALL route status operations to the correct provider based on `--provider`.\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: status with --provider agentcube\n274: - **GIVEN** the user runs `status --provider agentcube`\n275: - **WHEN** the status command executes\n276: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `StatusRuntime` with `provider=\"agentcube\"` and call `_get_cr_k8s_status`\n277: \n278: #### Scenario: status with --provider k8s\n279: - **GIVEN** the user runs `status --provider k8s`\n280: - **WHEN** the status command executes\n281: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `StatusRuntime` with `provider=\"k8s\"` and call `_get_k8s_status`\n282: \n283: ### Requirement: Invoke provider routing\n284: The system SHALL route invoke operations to the correct provider based on `--provider`.\n285: \n286: #### Scenario: invoke with --provider agentcube\n287: - **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke --provider agentcube`\n288: - **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n289: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `InvokeRuntime` with `provider=\"agentcube\"` and rewrite URL to AgentRuntime CR invocation path when `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n290: \n291: #### Scenario: invoke with --provider k8s\n292: - **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke --provider k8s`\n293: - **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n294: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `InvokeRuntime` with `provider=\"k8s\"` and invoke via standard deployment endpoint\n\n(End of file - total 294 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-026: K8s/AgentCube Provider — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n## Scope\n\nThis delta spec covers `KubernetesProvider` and `AgentCubeProvider` classes — their deployment, status retrieval, namespace management, name sanitization, CRD availability checks, and K8s client initialization error handling. Provider selection in CLI publish/status/invoke commands is also specified.\n\n---\n\n## KubernetesProvider\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider constructor\nThe system SHALL initialize `KubernetesProvider` with namespace, verbose flag, and optional kubeconfig path.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775867725307,"end":1775867725315}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775867725397,"sessionID":"ses_28609f618ffe4b3DGYsb2Pncn2","part":{"id":"prt_d79f70645001H508ojFtf29w5N","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d79f6f9d6001Fu6G4kEqQIygUC","sessionID":"ses_28609f618ffe4b3DGYsb2Pncn2","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":25791,"input":25683,"output":72,"reasoning":36,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.007266816}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775867726799,"sessionID":"ses_28609f618ffe4b3DGYsb2Pncn2","part":{"id":"prt_d79f70bcb001e8sw8LlAs8DBHV","messageID":"msg_d79f7066b001RYd1mzOBMCSpnO","sessionID":"ses_28609f618ffe4b3DGYsb2Pncn2","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867801385,"sessionID":"ses_28609f618ffe4b3DGYsb2Pncn2","part":{"id":"prt_d79f70f8a0010ULa0irDNO4GyB","messageID":"msg_d79f7066b001RYd1mzOBMCSpnO","sessionID":"ses_28609f618ffe4b3DGYsb2Pncn2","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_363bf74605924f028e332389","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `sdk-python`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n## Scope\n\nThis delta spec covers the HTTP client layer of the AgentCube Python SDK — session creation with connection pooling, control plane and data plane HTTP client contracts, header management, timeout behavior, error handling, and utility functions.\n\n---\n\n## HTTP Session Factory\n\n### Requirement: create_session\nThe system SHALL provide a `create_session` function that returns a `requests.Session` configured with connection pooling.\n\n#### Scenario: default pool parameters\n- **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called with no arguments\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** `HTTPAdapter(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)` SHALL be mounted for both `http://` and `https://` prefixes\n\n#### Scenario: custom pool parameters\n- **GIVEN** `create_session(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=50)` is called\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** both adapters SHALL use the provided pool parameters\n\n---\n\n## ControlPlaneClient\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient constructor\nThe system SHALL initialize `ControlPlaneClient` with URL resolution from arguments or environment, and auth token resolution from arguments or ServiceAccount file.\n\n#### Scenario: base URL from argument\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")`\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://wm:8080\"`\n\n#### Scenario: base URL from environment\n- **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` is `None` and env `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set to `\"http://wm-env:9090\"`\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://wm-env:9090\"`\n\n#### Scenario: auth token from argument\n- **GIVEN** `auth_token=\"my-token\"` is provided\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** `session.headers[\"Authorization\"]` SHALL be `\"Bearer my-token\"`\n\n#### Scenario: auth token from ServiceAccount file\n- **GIVEN** `auth_token` is `None` or empty and file `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` exists with content `\"sa-token\\n\"`\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** `session.headers[\"Authorization\"]` SHALL be `\"Bearer sa-token\"`\n\n#### Scenario: auth token file not found\n- **GIVEN** `auth_token` is `None` and the ServiceAccount token file does not exist\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** `read_token_from_file` returns `\"\"` and `Authorization` header SHALL NOT be set\n\n#### Scenario: empty token skips Authorization header\n- **GIVEN** resolved token is empty string\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** `session.headers` SHALL NOT contain `Authorization`\n\n#### Scenario: default Content-Type header\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized\n- **WHEN** session headers are inspected\n- **THEN** `session.headers[\"Content-Type\"]` SHALL be `\"application/json\"`\n\n#### Scenario: default timeout parameters\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is called with no timeout arguments\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL be `120` and `self.connect_timeout` SHALL be `5.0`\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient.create_session\nThe system SHALL POST to the Workload Manager to create a Code Interpreter session and return the session ID.\n\n#### Scenario: successful session creation\n- **GIVEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"ns\", ttl=7200, metadata={\"key\": \"val\"})`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\": \"test\", \"namespace\": \"ns\", \"ttl\": 7200, \"metadata\": {\"key\": \"val\"}}`\n\n#### Scenario: response contains sessionId\n- **GIVEN** the server returns `{\"data\": {\"sessionId\": \"abc-123\"}}`\n- **WHEN** the response is parsed\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `\"abc-123\"`\n\n#### Scenario: response missing sessionId\n- **GIVEN** the server returns `{\"data\": {}}`\n- **WHEN** the response is parsed\n- **THEN** the method SHALL raise `ValueError`\n\n#### Scenario: request timeout tuple\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`\n- **WHEN** any request is sent\n- **THEN** the `timeout` parameter SHALL be `(5.0, 120)`\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient.delete_session\nThe system SHALL DELETE a session and treat 404 as success.\n\n#### Scenario: successful deletion\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"sess-1\")` returns HTTP 200\n- **WHEN** the response is processed\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n\n#### Scenario: 404 treated as success\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"nonexistent\")` returns HTTP 404\n- **WHEN** the response is processed\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n\n#### Scenario: other error logged and returns False\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"sess-1\")` returns HTTP 500\n- **WHEN** the response is processed\n- **THEN** the method SHALL log a warning and return `False`\n\n### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient.close\nThe system SHALL release the underlying HTTP session.\n\n#### Scenario: close releases session\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.close()` is called\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** `self.session.close()` SHALL be called\n\n---\n\n## CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient constructor\nThe system SHALL initialize the data plane client with base URL derived from router URL or explicit `base_url`.\n\n#### Scenario: base URL from router URL\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:8080\", namespace=\"ns\", cr_name=\"my-interpreter\")`\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/ns/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/\"`\n\n#### Scenario: base URL explicit override\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://custom/url/\")`\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://custom/url/\"` and router/namespace/cr_name SHALL be ignored for URL construction\n\n#### Scenario: session header set\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"sess-1\")`\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** `session.headers[\"x-agentcube-session-id\"]` SHALL be `\"sess-1\"`\n\n#### Scenario: default timeouts\n- **GIVEN** no timeout arguments provided\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL be `120` and `self.connect_timeout` SHALL be `5.0`\n\n### Requirement: _request method\nThe system SHALL send HTTP requests with appropriate headers based on whether a body is present.\n\n#### Scenario: JSON body request\n- **GIVEN** `_request(\"POST\", \"api/execute\", body=b'{\"cmd\": \"ls\"}')`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** `Content-Type: application/json` SHALL be set on the request and URL SHALL be `urljoin(self.base_url, \"api/execute\")`\n\n#### Scenario: request without body\n- **GIVEN** `_request(\"GET\", \"api/files\")`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** no `Content-Type` override SHALL be set (session defaults apply)\n\n### Requirement: execute_command\nThe system SHALL POST to `api/execute` with command and timeout, adding a 2-second buffer to read timeout.\n\n#### Scenario: command with explicit timeout\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=10.0)`\n- **WHEN** the request is built\n- **THEN** HTTP read timeout SHALL be `12.0` (`timeout + 2.0`) and body SHALL contain `{\"command\": [\"sleep 10\"], \"timeout\": \"10s\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: command with default timeout\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"ls\", timeout=None)` and `self.timeout` is `120`\n- **WHEN** the request is built\n- **THEN** effective timeout SHALL be `120` and body SHALL contain `\"timeout\": \"120s\"`\n\n#### Scenario: command string split into list\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"ls -la\")`\n- **WHEN** the body is constructed\n- **THEN** `command` field SHALL be `[\"ls\", \"-la\"]` (split by whitespace)\n\n#### Scenario: non-zero exit code raises error\n- **GIVEN** response JSON is `{\"exit_code\": 1, \"stderr\": \"error\", \"stdout\": \"\"}`\n- **WHEN** the response is processed\n- **THEN** `CommandExecutionError(exit_code=1, stderr=\"error\", command=\"ls\")` SHALL be raised\n\n### Requirement: run_code\nThe system SHALL write code to a timestamped file and execute it via the interpreter.\n\n#### Scenario: Python code execution\n- **GIVEN** `run_code(\"python\", \"print('hi')\")`\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `write_file` with a timestamped `.py` file, then `execute_command(\"python3 <file>\")`\n\n#### Scenario: language alias normalization\n- **GIVEN** `language` is `\"py\"` or `\"python3\"`\n- **WHEN** `run_code` executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL be treated as Python and follow the same path as `\"python\"`\n\n### Requirement: write_file\nThe system SHALL POST base64-encoded content to `api/files`.\n\n#### Scenario: write file with base64 content\n- **GIVEN** `write_file(\"hello\", \"/tmp/test.txt\")`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** POST `api/files` with JSON body `{\"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"content\": \"<base64 of 'hello'>\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}`\n\n### Requirement: upload_file\nThe system SHALL POST multipart form data to `api/files` with session header.\n\n#### Scenario: multipart upload\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file(\"/local/file.txt\", \"/remote/path.txt\")`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** POST `api/files` with `files={'file': open('/local/file.txt', 'rb')}`, `data={'path': '/remote/path.txt', 'mode': '0644'}`, and header `x-agentcube-session-id` explicitly set\n\n### Requirement: download_file\nThe system SHALL GET file content with streaming and write to local path.\n\n#### Scenario: streaming download\n- **GIVEN** `download_file(\"/remote/path.txt\", \"/local/out.txt\")`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** GET `api/files/remote/path.txt` (with `lstrip(\"/\")`), `stream=True`, and content SHALL be written in chunks to `/local/out.txt`\n\n#### Scenario: clean path strips leading slash\n- **GIVEN** `remote_path = \"/absolute/path.txt\"`\n- **WHEN** download URL is constructed\n- **THEN** `clean_path` SHALL be `\"absolute/path.txt\"`\n\n### Requirement: list_files\nThe system SHALL GET file listing with path query parameter.\n\n#### Scenario: list files in path\n- **GIVEN** `list_files(\"/some/path\")`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** GET `api/files?path=/some/path`\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.close\nThe system SHALL release the underlying HTTP session.\n\n#### Scenario: close releases session\n- **GIVEN** `close()` is called\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** `self.session.close()` SHALL be called\n\n---\n\n## AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructor\nThe system SHALL initialize the agent runtime data plane client with invocation base URL.\n\n#### Scenario: base URL construction\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:8080\", namespace=\"ns\", agent_name=\"my-agent\")`\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/ns/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/\"`\n\n#### Scenario: SESSION_HEADER class constant\n- **GIVEN** the class definition\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.SESSION_HEADER` is accessed\n- **THEN** the value SHALL be `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n\n### Requirement: bootstrap_session_id\nThe system SHALL GET the invocation base URL and extract session ID from response header.\n\n#### Scenario: session ID extracted from header\n- **GIVEN** GET `{base_url}` returns response with header `x-agentcube-session-id: \"new-session\"`\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `\"new-session\"`\n\n#### Scenario: missing session ID header raises error\n- **GIVEN** GET `{base_url}` response does not contain `x-agentcube-session-id`\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")`\n\n### Requirement: invoke\nThe system SHALL POST JSON payload to the invocation base URL with session header.\n\n#### Scenario: invoke with session header\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"s1\", payload={\"msg\": \"hello\"})`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** POST `{base_url}` with headers `x-agentcube-session-id: s1` and `Content-Type: application/json`, body SHALL be JSON `{\"msg\": \"hello\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: invoke with default timeout\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(\"s1\", payload, timeout=None)`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `self.timeout=120`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(5.0, 120)`\n\n#### Scenario: invoke with custom timeout\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(\"s1\", payload, timeout=60.0)`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(5.0, 60.0)`\n\n#### Scenario: invoke without session_id raises error\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or empty string\n- **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.close\nThe system SHALL release the underlying HTTP session.\n\n#### Scenario: close releases session\n- **GIVEN** `close()` is called\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** `self.session.close()` SHALL be called\n\n---\n\n## Connection Pool Reuse\n\n### Requirement: Session reuse within client\nThe system SHALL reuse a single `requests.Session` instance per client for all HTTP operations.\n\n#### Scenario: same session for multiple requests\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` calls `create_session` then `delete_session`\n- **WHEN** both requests are sent\n- **THEN** they SHALL use the same `self.session` instance\n\n#### Scenario: independent sessions across clients\n- **GIVEN** two `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` instances are created\n- **WHEN** their session objects are compared\n- **THEN** `client1.session` and `client2.session` SHALL be different objects\n\n---\n\n## Utility Functions\n\n### Requirement: read_token_from_file\nThe system SHALL read and strip token content from a file, returning empty string on missing file.\n\n#### Scenario: file exists with trailing newline\n- **GIVEN** file `/tmp/token` contains `\"my-token\\n\"`\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/tmp/token\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `\"my-token\"`\n\n#### Scenario: file not found\n- **GIVEN** file `/tmp/nonexistent` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/tmp/nonexistent\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `\"\"`\n\n### Requirement: get_logger\nThe system SHALL create a named logger with configurable level.\n\n#### Scenario: logger with custom level\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"test_module\", level=\"DEBUG\")`\n- **WHEN** the function executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a Logger named `\"test_module\"` with level `DEBUG`\n\n---\n\n## Exception Hierarchy\n\n### Requirement: Exception classes\nThe system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n\n#### Scenario: CommandExecutionError attributes\n- **GIVEN** `CommandExecutionError(exit_code=1, stderr=\"err\", command=\"ls\")`\n- **WHEN** the exception is created\n- **THEN** `exc.exit_code` SHALL be `1`, `exc.stderr` SHALL be `\"err\"`, `exc.command` SHALL be `\"ls\"`, and `str(exc)` SHALL contain `\"Command failed (exit 1): err\"`\n\n#### Scenario: exception inheritance\n- **GIVEN** the exception classes are defined\n- **WHEN** inheritance is checked\n- **THEN** `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` SHALL all be subclasses of `AgentCubeError`\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775867801319,"end":1775867801383}}}}
